> I don't like using 0 as a special marker value here - wouldn't 0 be a perfectly good tweak value?
> Maybe add an explicit method `resetWithRandomTweak()`?

Well, I'm expecting people to always be using the random tweak provided
except in testing.

Why would you need a specific tweak given the internal use-case?

