body:
I've been bitten in the past by these kind of 'special values' unexpectedly turning up, so I'm just cautious and trying to avoid technical debt. 
If it's really only for testing, maybe the method that takes an explicit tweak should be the explicitly named one. Eg.
```c++
void CRollingBloomFilter::reset()
{
    resetWithTweak(GetRand(std::numeric_limits<unsigned int>::max()));
}
void CRollingBloomFilter::resetWithTweak(unsigned int nNewTweak)
{
    ...
}
```

